race.comment: CENTENARIO (8) settled back in the field then worked home well without threatening first-up over 1550m at this track. Improved sharply to win second-up on a heavy track here last prep. Proven at this trip and after enjoying a nice trail just off the speed will prove tough to stop. SUIT OF ARMOUR (6) returned from two years on the sidelines with a respectable fifth in the same race as CENTENARIO a fortnight ago. Will enjoy the step up in distance and with that comeback race now under the belt he looks a genuine winning hope. The consistent KENMARE BAY (9) charged home to score over 1550m here two back then again attacked the line when third over 1800m at the Kensington track most recently. Won here at this trip last prep. Rock hard fit and should be in the finish. PLEASURE ARTIST (5) won a BM72 here at 1900m just before Xmas then failed in better company before a six-week let-up. Each-way chance. MIRRA IMPACT (7) is racing well and gets some weight relief in this harder race.
